 Davido. Photo Idris Dawodu for Guardian Life Davido has taken to Twitter to shade his cousin Bamidele Adeleke for declaring his interest to run in the 2022 Osun State gubernatorial election accusing him of ‘forming intellectual.’ In his tweet, Davido shared a picture of his cousin posing with a provisional clearance certificate for the Osun State gubernatorial election. He wrote, “Wonderful! I finished university with a 2:1. But it’s now cousin Dele who struggled to even get a 2:2 that is now forming ‘intellectual’.” Wonderful! Me I finished uni with a 2:1. But it’s now cousin dele who struggled to even get a 2:2 that is now forming “intellectual”. Intellectual that has not succeeded in building one single thing in his life on his own. This life ehn! Osun beware of FAKES! @deleadeleke001 pic.twitter.com/FwrlKNKLF0 — Davido (@davido) January 18, 2022 Davido also accused his cousin of not building anything on his own and being a ‘bad belle.’ “Intellectual that has not succeeded in building one single thing in his own life on his own. This life ehn! Osun beware of FAKES. @deleadeleke001” “Bad belle lopo laiye Kehinde Le je oju taiye,” he tweeted. Last month, Davido’s uncle Senator Ademola Adeleke (the dancing senator), reportedly submitted his gubernatorial nomination form at the PDP office, announcing his candidacy for his Osun State gubernatorial election. The singer also posted a screenshot from Bamidele Adeleke’s Instagram shows him (Bamidele) expressing appreciation to Ademola for taking him under his wing. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1645234 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/IMG-1767-513x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1492" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/IMG-1767-513x598.jpg 513w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/IMG-1767-206x240.jpg 206w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/IMG-1767-412x480.jpg 412w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/IMG-1767-515x600.jpg 515w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/IMG-1767.jpg 719w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Bamidele shared a picture with Ademola in the screenshot, captioning it, “Celebrating my dear uncle and father figure. “You took me under your wings as I passed out of high school and raised me like your own son.. Whatever I am ir achieve, I owe to God and you. I can never thank you enough.” Ademola Adeleke taking to Twitter, quoted the tweet saying, “Don’t worry nephew God got us #IMOLEDE #OSUN2022”, which Davido retweeted.